Move 1: Immediate Budget Reallocation (The 20% Shift)
Action: Shift 20% of the ad spend currently allocated to Google Ads and Direct channels over to LinkedIn and Referral/Affiliate programs.
Impact: Since LinkedIn acquires customers at less than half the cost of Google Ads, this immediate shift will lower the blended CPA and push the overall ROAS closer to 2.0x without requiring additional budget.

Move 2: Emergency Mobile UX Audit
Action: Instruct the web development and UX teams to conduct a friction audit on the mobile landing pages and checkout flows.
Impact: Mobile users are showing interest by clicking the ads, but dropping off on the site. Fixing mobile responsiveness to match Desktop conversion rates would instantly yield a ~30% increase in total customers.

Move 3: Fix the Stage 1 "Lead Capture" Offer
Action: Because 83% of visitors bounce without leaving their information, we must improve our Top-of-Funnel (ToFu) lead magnets. Implement lower-friction signup forms (e.g., "Sign up with Google/LinkedIn" buttons) and gate high-value content (like the successful Tech Webinars) behind an email capture wall.

Move 4: Restructure the "Brand Awareness" Strategy
Action: Stop expecting immediate bottom-of-funnel conversions from the Brand_Awareness_2025 campaign. Instead, tag these visitors with a retargeting pixel and funnel them into the highly successful Retargeting_Q1 or Webinar_Series_Tech campaigns to nurture them over a longer time horizon.
